Make kinetic (fling) deceleration friction tunable for touch momentum.

Device-measured root cause of "APZ momentum doesn't work" on this WPE build:
async scrolling and the kinetic fling both actually function (screenshots show
the feed coasting after finger-release), but the fling is far too short/abrupt.
ScrollAnimationKinetic uses offset(t) = x0 + (v/friction)(1 - e^-friction*t), so
total coast distance = velocity/friction and the time-constant = 1/friction.
Upstream hardcodes friction=4 (desktop trackpad/wheel tuning): a hard touch flick
(measured initial velocity ~5800 px/s) coasts only ~1450px and dumps ~75% of that
in the first ~0.35s, so it feels like it stops dead = "no momentum".

Make it tunable via WEBKIT_KINETIC_DECEL_FRICTION (range 0.3..8, default 4 =
upstream). Lower values give a longer, smoother glide suited to phone touch
flicking; the browser sets the device default in apps/browser/main.cpp.
